{{Infobox language |name = Dema |nativename = |pronunciation = |states = [[Mozambique]] |region = |speakers = 5,000 |date = 2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor= Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid languages|Southern]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] |fam6=[[Shona language|Shona]] (S.10) |iso3=dmx |glotto=dema1235 |glottorefname=Dema }}
'''Dema''' is a [[Bantu language]] of Mozambique. It is closely related to [[Shona language|Shona]]. The population has been displaced by the construction of a dam.
